h3. Issue Summary
When using https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/confluence/jsapi/confluence/ like:

```
When getting the Macro using 
AP.confluence.getMacroData(function(data){
alert(data);
});
```

it previously returns an `undefined` when no information is associated to Macro. But now it returns  {"":undefined} which is causing our apps to break:

 !Excellentable Code Exec.png| height=250! 

h3. Expected Results
Undefined

h3. Actual Results
{"": undefined}

h3. Workaround
Update conditions to new result

Reported by one of our plain text macro vendors ...

 
The data returned from AP.confluence.getMacroData() differs depending on whether the macro was created in the old or new editor.
 
For pages that use the old editor, the data returned is like this  (assume a macro with two parameters, called “parameter1” and “parameter2”):
 
{
  “parameter1”: “value1”,
  “parameter2”: “value2”
}
 
For pages that use the new editor, the data returned is like this:
 
{
  “parameter1”: {
    “value”: “value1”
  },
  “parameter2:” {
    “value”: “value2”
  }
}
 
(i.e. for the old editor the data returned is an object with plain old key/value pairs;  for the new editor the values are objects that have a “value” property).
 
The vendor can work around this by checking which format they're given but the consumer of the API shouldn't need to worry about such details. It should be a consistent format regardless of which editor is used.

As far as I know, it saves space when referencing an image that is already on another Confluence page. Therefore I created a confluence page PICTURES where I stored all pictures often used.

{color:#ff8b00}_Is it right, that each time I upload a picture a new file is uploaded? If I use a specific picture on many, many pages and I upload it for each page, it is multiple times in my space?_{color}

