h3. Issue Summary
Fixed headers are a useful resource on Confluence when we have a huge table and need to scroll it down to the bottom of the content, so it helps us to read the table content properly. However, if it is inside a single Page Layout and there is another Page Layout in the page, this resource doesn't work - as well as if the Page Layout is a double or triple one.

h3. Environment
* Cloud
* Old editing experience

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page;
# Add a Page Layout;
# Add a long table inside the layout;
# Set it with row header;
# Add a new Page Layout below the existing one/change the current layout to a double one;
# Add some content in the new layout;
# Publish the page and scroll down the screen.

h3. Expected Results
The table header is fixed in the screen while you are scrolling it.

h3. Actual Results
The entire table is scrolled out.

h3. Workaround
Don't use the page layouts if you wish to have this resource.

h3. Summary 
Team Calendar doesn't display Oauth prompt for JIRA Events

h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Install Confluence Team Calendars;
 # Create an Application Link between Confluence and JIRA;
 # Create a Calendar;
 # Click Add Event and try to select a JIRA EVENT TYPE;

h3. Expected behavior
It shows "Login & Approve" message

h3. Actual behavior
Calendars are loaded with errors.

*Workaround*
 # Insert a JIRA Issues macro into a page;
 # => it shows "Login & Approve" message;
 # Authenticate;
 # Back in the calendar, the JIRA Events work properly.
